    public abstract class AbstractCooldownItem
extends AbstractCustomItem
    A AbstractCustomItem that has a single cooldown associated with it. If your custom item requires multiple cooldowns for the item, or a more sophisticated system you should extend AbstractCustomItem

      • playerOnCooldown

        public boolean playerOnCooldown(org.bukkit.entity.Player player)
        Checks whether the player is on cooldown. If the player is off cooldown, they will be put on cooldown and false will be returned. If the player is on cooldown, they will be sent a message with the remaining cooldown and true is returned. Call this method wherever necessary in your custom item implementation
        Parameters:
        player - player
        Returns:
        true/false
